#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting Cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cockpit is included in the delivered pre-built images, or can be installed if you are installing your own instances manually. For details regarding the manual installation, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-settings-software\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "Though Cockpit is present in the pre-built images by default, the plugin for administration of virtual machines needs to be installed manually. You can do so by installing the <literal>microos-cockpit</literal> pattern as described below. You can also use the following command in case Cockpit is not installed on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;transactional-update pkg install -t pattern microos-cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reboot your machine to switch to the latest snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cockpit's plugins installed from the <literal>microos-cockpit</literal> pattern may differ according to technologies installed on your system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "The plugin <literal>Podman containers</literal> is installed only if the <emphasis>Containers Runtime for non-clustered systems</emphasis> patterns are installed on your system. Similarly, the <literal>Virtual Machines</literal> plugin is installed only if the <emphasis>KVM Virtualization Host</emphasis> pattern is installed on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the Cockpit instance is intended to serve as a primary one, you need to enable the Cockpit socket in &systemd; by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "After running the command, the server will expose the default <emphasis>9090</emphasis> port. &systemd; will start the <literal>cockpit-ws</literal> service that listens on the 9090 port."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case you have enabled the firewall, you must also open the firewall for Cockpit as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=cockpit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "And then reload the firewall configuration by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;firewall-cmd --reload"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro_cockpit.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now you can access the Cockpit web interface by opening the following address in your web browser:"
msgstr ""

